<p>This is not necessarily a good assumption. “Untuned” and “Functional” is usually mutually exclusive when it comes to <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> gains. An incorrect P gain can cause any symptom from no motion at all, to rapid and uncontrolled motion.</p>
